6. Realistic Research Program (10 Years)

Phase 1: Foundation (Years 1-3)

Goal: Rigorous results for lower dimensions and simplified models.

Projects:

1. Complete constructive proof for 2D Yang-Mills using heat kernel methods.
2. Prove mass gap for 3D Yang-Mills using cluster expansion and RG.
3. Develop efficient tensor network algorithms for (2+1)D gauge theories.

Mathematical Tools:

· Cluster expansion with improved convergence bounds
· Reflection positivity proofs for various formulations
· Exact solutions for large-N matrix models

Phase 2: Approximation with Control (Years 4-6)

Goal: Controlled approximations to 4D theory.

Projects:

1. Solve large-N master field equations numerically with error bounds.
2. Implement numerical bootstrap for glueball spectrum in planar limit.
3. Develop stochastic quantization with proven convergence.

Mathematical Tools:

· Interval arithmetic for rigorous numerics
· Borel resummation of 1/N expansion
· Complex Langevin convergence proofs

Phase 3: Interpolation and Synthesis (Years 7-10)

Goal: Bridge from controlled limits to physical SU(3).

Projects:

1. Prove existence of 4D SU(2) theory via RG flow from 5D.
2. Develop resurgent trans-series for 1/N expansion to reach N=3.
3. Combine bootstrap, lattice, and analytic methods for complete proof.

Mathematical Tools:

· Dimensional continuation and ε-expansion
· Resurgence theory and trans-asymptotic matching
· Categorical formulation of duality

