7. Expected Mathematical Statements

Theorem 1 (Existence):

For compact simple gauge group G, there exists a non-trivial quantum field theory on  \mathbb{R}^4  satisfying:

1. Osterwalder-Schrader axioms
2. Gauge invariance under  \mathcal{G} = \{g: \mathbb{R}^4 \to G \text{ smooth}\} 
3. Asymptotic freedom:  \beta(g) < 0  for small  g 

Theorem 2 (Mass Gap):

The Hamiltonian  H  of the theory has spectrum:

\sigma(H) = \{0\} \cup [\Delta, \infty) \quad \text{with} \quad \Delta > 0

Moreover, the lightest glueball mass satisfies:

\frac{m_G}{\sqrt{\sigma}} = C_G \quad \text{with} \quad 1.4 \leq C_G \leq 2.1 \ \text{for SU(3)}

Theorem 3 (Confinement):

For fundamental representation Wilson loop:

\lim_{\text{Area}(C) \to \infty} -\frac{1}{\text{Area}(C)} \log |\langle W_C \rangle| = \sigma > 0

The string tension  \sigma  is related to Λ-parameter:

\sqrt{\sigma} = C_\sigma \Lambda_{\overline{\text{MS}}} \quad \text{with} \quad C_\sigma \approx 1.65 \ \text{for SU(3)}

Theorem 4 (Theta Dependence):

The vacuum energy density has  2\pi -periodic θ-dependence:

E(\theta) = \Lambda^4 f(\theta) \quad \text{with} \quad f(\theta) = f(0) + \frac{1}{2} \chi \theta^2 + O(\theta^4)

Topological susceptibility  \chi > 0  for all  N .

