8.2 Physical Validation

Glueball Spectrum:

m_{0^{++}} = 1710 \pm 50 \ \text{MeV}, \quad m_{2^{++}} = 2390 \pm 100 \ \text{MeV}, \quad m_{0^{-+}} = 2560 \pm 120 \ \text{MeV}

String Tension: From quarkonium spectroscopy:

\sqrt{\sigma} = 440 \pm 20 \ \text{MeV}

Deconfinement Temperature:

T_c / \sqrt{\sigma} = 0.63 \pm 0.02 \quad \Rightarrow \quad T_c \approx 277 \ \text{MeV}

8.3 Predictions for Testing

New Glueballs: Predict masses for  1^{+-}, 2^{-+}, 3^{++}  states.

Finite Temperature: Equation of state  p(T)/T^4 , screening masses.

Large-N Scaling:  m_G(N)/\sqrt{\sigma(N)}  as function of 1/N².

