APPENDICES TO THE YANG-MILLS EXISTENCE AND MASS GAP RESEARCH PROGRAM

Appendix A: Mathematical Foundations of Simplicial Lattice Gauge Theory

A.1 Regge Calculus and Piecewise-Flat Manifolds

A 4-dimensional simplicial complex  K  approximates a smooth manifold  M  via piecewise-linear geometry.

Metric on a 4-Simplex:
For a 4-simplex  \sigma  with vertices  v_0, v_1, v_2, v_3, v_4 , the geometry is determined by the 10 edge lengths  \ell_{ij} = |v_i - v_j| . The interior flat metric in barycentric coordinates  (\xi^0, \xi^1, \xi^2, \xi^3, \xi^4)  with  \sum \xi^i = 1  is:

ds^2 = \sum_{0 \leq i < j \leq 4} \ell_{ij}^2 d\xi^i d\xi^j

Regge Action (Discrete Einstein-Hilbert):

S_{\text{Regge}} = \frac{1}{8\pi G} \sum_{h \in K^{(2)}} A_h \delta_h

where  h  are triangular hinges (2-simplices),  A_h  is area,  \delta_h  is deficit angle.

A.2 Gauge Theory on Simplicial Complex

Discrete Connection: Associate group elements  U_e \in G  to edges  e \in K^{(1)} .

Discrete Curvature: For triangle  t \in K^{(2)}  with boundary edges  e_1, e_2, e_3 :

U_t = U_{e_1} U_{e_2} U_{e_3}^{-1}

represents holonomy around  t .

4D Simplex Action: For 4-simplex  \sigma  with boundary tetrahedra  \tau_1, \ldots, \tau_5 :

S_\sigma = \frac{\beta}{N} \sum_{\text{triangles } t \subset \partial\sigma} \left[ 1 - \frac{1}{N} \text{Re tr } U_t \right] V_t

where  V_t  is the dual area associated with triangle  t .

Advantage over Hypercubic Lattice:

· Better rotational symmetry:  S_4  symmetry of 4-simplex vs  S_4  broken to  \mathbb{Z}_2^4  for hypercube
· Natural for coupling to gravity via  \beta \sim 1/g^2  becoming dynamical
· No fermion doubling problem in chiral theories

A.3 Reflection Positivity Proof

Temporal Foliation: Choose time function  t: K^{(0)} \to \mathbb{R}  separating vertices into:

t^{-1}(0) = \text{spatial slice}, \quad t^{-1}(\mathbb{R}^+) = \text{future}, \quad t^{-1}(\mathbb{R}^-) = \text{past}

Reflection Operator  \theta : Maps  t \to -t , complex conjugates group elements on temporal edges.

Theorem A.3.1: The simplicial Yang-Mills action  S_{\text{simp}} = \sum_{\sigma} S_\sigma  satisfies:

\langle \theta F \cdot F \rangle \geq 0 \quad \forall F \text{ depending on edges with } t > 0

Proof:

1. Decompose action:  S = S_+ + S_- + S_0  where  S_\pm  involve simplices entirely in  t \gtrless 0 ,  S_0  straddles  t=0 
2. In temporal gauge  U_{\text{time-like edges}} = \mathbb{1} , simplices straddling  t=0  have  U_t = \mathbb{1}  ⇒  S_0 = 0 
3. Measure factorizes:  d\mu = d\mu_+ d\mu_0 d\mu_- 
4. Therefore:

\langle \theta F F \rangle = \int d\mu_0 \left| \int d\mu_+ F e^{-S_+} \right|^2 \geq 0

