Appendix G: Mathematical Proof Checklist

G.1 Existence Proof Requirements

Lattice Construction:

· Define Wilson action on finite lattice  \Lambda_{L,a} 
· Prove reflection positivity
· Establish thermodynamic limit  L\to\infty 
· Prove uniqueness of infinite-volume measure

Continuum Limit:

· Define renormalized coupling  g_R(\mu) 
· Prove existence of critical trajectory  \beta_c(a) 
· Show correlation functions have finite limits
· Verify Osterwalder-Schrader axioms in continuum

Gauge Invariance:

· Construct gauge-invariant algebra of observables
· Show physical Hilbert space = gauge-invariant states
· Prove BRST invariance in continuum

G.2 Mass Gap Proof Requirements

Correlation Decay:

· Prove  |\langle \mathcal{O}(x)\mathcal{O}(y)\rangle_c| \leq C e^{-m|x-y|} 
· Show  m > 0  uniformly in volume
· Relate to spectral gap via OS reconstruction

Spectral Analysis:

· Construct Hamiltonian  H  from transfer matrix
· Prove  H \geq 0  with unique ground state
· Show  \sigma(H) \subset \{0\} \cup [\Delta, \infty) ,  \Delta > 0 

Alternative Approaches:

· Cheeger constant proof:  h > 0 \Rightarrow \Delta \geq h^2/(8D) 
· Large-N proof: solve master field, control 1/N expansion
· Bootstrap proof: bound  \Delta_{\min}  from unitarity

G.3 Confinement Proof Requirements

Wilson Loop:

· Define  W_C = \text{tr} P e^{i\oint_C A} 
· Prove area law:  \langle W_C \rangle \sim e^{-\sigma \text{Area}(C)}  for large C
· Show  \sigma > 0 

Dual Superconductor:

· Construct dual theory via transformation
· Prove monopole condensation  \langle \phi \rangle \neq 0 
· Show dual photon gets mass via Higgs mechanism

Symmetry Breaking:

· Identify 1-form center symmetry  \mathbb{Z}_N^{(1)} 
· Prove spontaneous breaking in confined phase
· Relate to area law via order parameter

G.4 Numerical Verification Checklist

Lattice Simulations:

· Multiple lattice sizes:  16^4, 24^4, 32^4, 48^4 
· Multiple  \beta  values for continuum extrapolation
· Check autocorrelation times, thermalization
· Independent codes for cross-checking

Error Analysis:

· Statistical errors: jackknife/bootstrap
· Systematic: finite volume, discretization, scale setting
· Total error: combine all sources with correlations

Consistency Checks:

· Compare with perturbation theory at high energy
· Check large-N predictions
· Verify with other methods (bootstrap, tensor networks)

G.5 Cross-Method Validation

Triangulation of Proof:

· Constructive QFT: existence + basic properties
· Large-N: exact results in limit + 1/N expansion
· Numerical: quantitative results with errors
· Bootstrap: rigorous bounds on dimensions
· Tensor networks: Hamiltonian spectrum
· Stochastic quantization: alternative formulation

Convergence Criteria:
All methods must agree within errors on:

·  m_{0^{++}}/\sqrt{\sigma} \approx 3.56(11) 
·  \sqrt{\sigma}/\Lambda_{\overline{\text{MS}}} \approx 1.65(5) 
·  T_c/\sqrt{\sigma} \approx 0.63(2) 

